    {
      "annotations": [
        {
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The overall spirit of the song - written for Israeli toops in the Yom Kippur War, it is for strengthening Jewish identity in the face of adversity and moral ambiguity. LC does claim that the song is for \"both sides\", and indeed it is true for any people in this struggle.",
              "kind": "text"
            }
          ],
          "id": "1"
        }
      ],
      "anchor": {
        "kind": "fragment",
        "documentId": "song.lover_lover_lover",
        "fragmentId": "25"
      }
    },
    {
      "annotations": [
        {
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "In summary this song is a dialogue between God and the Jewish people. The Jew cries out \"God, why have you abandoned me? How have you allowed us to fall into such a wretched condition? Give us a fresh start, let us escape it!\". And God replies \"It was you who forgot me, I never left you. I have given everything that you need.\"",
              "kind": "text"
            }
          ],
          "id": "1"
        }
      ],
      "anchor": {
        "kind": "fragment",
        "documentId": "song.lover_lover_lover",
